  "articles": [
    {
      "id": "b0c1d2e3-f4a5-4789-90ab-cdef00000001",
      "title": "Drop 02: Field Notes",
      "slug": "drop-02-field-notes",
      "category": "Drops",
      "author": "Editorial Team",
      "featured": true,
      "readTime": 4,
      "publishedAt": "2026-05-12T10:00:00.000Z",
      "excerpt": "Five new silhouettes, three returning favourites.",
      "description": "A first look at the second drop of FW 26 — the parka, the bomber, and the pieces bridging studio and street.",
      "image": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1483721310020-03333e577078?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1600",
      "content": "<p>FW 26 / Drop 02 lands today. Five new silhouettes, three restocks, one quiet idea: the line between studio and street has been blurred for a while, and the wardrobe should reflect that.</p><h2>What dropped</h2><ul><li><strong>Volt Halo Parka</strong> — our heaviest outerwear of the season.</li><li><strong>Volt Vault Coach</strong> — the heavier coach silhouette.</li><li><strong>Volt Reach Vest</strong> — the most-asked-for piece.</li><li><strong>Volt Slope Pant</strong> — wide-leg cousin to the Mile.</li><li><strong>Volt Drift Tee</strong> — the boxy Atlas.</li></ul><h2>What is back</h2><p>The Marker Cap returns in three colourways. The Pacer Hoodie is restocked in Heather Grey. The Atlas Tee is back across all sizes.</p><blockquote>Move differently.</blockquote>"
    },
    {
      "id": "b0c1d2e3-f4a5-4789-90ab-cdef00000002",
      "title": "Studio Diary: The Coach Jacket",
      "slug": "studio-diary-the-coach-jacket",
      "category": "Behind The Scenes",
      "author": "Studio Team",
      "featured": false,
      "readTime": 5,
      "publishedAt": "2026-05-08T14:30:00.000Z",
      "excerpt": "Three patterns, two fabrics, one quiet revelation about durability.",
      "description": "How a single garment got rebuilt three times before it shipped — a studio diary on the Beacon Jacket.",
      "image": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1556906781-9a412961c28c?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1600",
      "content": "<p>The Beacon Jacket went through three pattern revisions before we cut a single production unit.</p><h2>Pattern 01 — Too boxy</h2><p>The first attempt was a one-for-one homage. Honest fit, broad shoulders, nobody on the team wore it twice.</p><h2>Pattern 02 — Too sharp</h2><p>We tapered the waist. The result felt like a club jacket, not a coach.</p><h2>Pattern 03 — Field</h2><p>The final pattern keeps the dropped shoulder, broadens the hem by 4 cm, and shaves 1.5 cm off the sleeve. The fabric is a 3-layer ripstop with a brushed flannel back. It moves with you without feeling like a costume.</p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "b0c1d2e3-f4a5-4789-90ab-cdef00000003",
      "title": "What Makes a Performance Tee",
      "slug": "what-makes-a-performance-tee",
      "category": "Tech",
      "author": "Product Team",
      "featured": true,
      "readTime": 4,
      "publishedAt": "2026-05-05T09:00:00.000Z",
      "excerpt": "Modal blends, brushed finishes, moisture management — the Atlas, taken apart.",
      "description": "Why the Volt Atlas Tee uses 95% cotton modal and not 100% cotton — and what that means when you actually move in it.",
      "image": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1521572163474-6864f9cf17ab?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1600",
      "content": "<p>If you have ever wondered why high-end sportswear costs what it does, the answer is buried in the spec sheet. Here is ours, demystified.</p><h2>The fabric</h2><p>95% cotton, 5% elastane. Cotton-modal jersey, 180 gsm. Loomed in Portugal. The elastane is what gives the tee its recovery.</p><h2>The finish</h2><p>A reactive moisture-wicking treatment is bonded to the yarn before knit. Unlike spray-on treatments, this one survives the wash cycle.</p><h2>What you feel</h2><p>Soft hand, no clinginess. Performs like a base layer, wears like an heirloom.</p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "b0c1d2e3-f4a5-4789-90ab-cdef00000004",
      "title": "Layering, Reduced to Four",
      "slug": "layering-reduced-to-four",
      "category": "Style",
      "author": "Editorial Team",
      "featured": false,
      "readTime": 5,
      "publishedAt": "2026-04-30T11:15:00.000Z",
      "excerpt": "Four layers, ten pieces. The dressing principle behind the collection.",
      "description": "A simple framework for building a wardrobe that survives the seasonal swing.",
      "image": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1483985988355-763728e1935b?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1600",
      "content": "<p>Most of us own too many clothes and wear too few. The fix is not buying less — it is buying with intent.</p><h2>01 — Base</h2><p>The Atlas Tee. The Anchor Crew. These touch your skin. Comfort matters more than statement.</p><h2>02 — Mid</h2><p>The Pacer Hoodie. The Echo Hoodie. Warmth without bulk. Sleeve length is everything.</p><h2>03 — Shell</h2><p>The Beacon Jacket. The Vault Coach. The Reach Vest. Face the weather. Choose by weight, not by colour.</p><h2>04 — Hero</h2><p>The Halo Parka. This is what people see first. Make sure it deserves the attention.</p><blockquote>Ten pieces, worn well, beats forty worn once.</blockquote>"
    },
    {
      "id": "b0c1d2e3-f4a5-4789-90ab-cdef00000005",
      "title": "Restocked: Logo Cap, Three Ways",
      "slug": "restocked-logo-cap-three-ways",
      "category": "Restocks",
      "author": "Editorial Team",
      "featured": false,
      "readTime": 2,
      "publishedAt": "2026-04-20T08:45:00.000Z",
      "excerpt": "Marker Cap returns in Black, Cream, and Cobalt.",
      "description": "The six-panel Volt Marker Cap is back — and we tightened the strap.",
      "image": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1588850561407-ed78c282e89b?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1600",
      "content": "<p>The Marker Cap sold through its first run in eleven days. Here is what changed for the restock.</p><h2>New hardware</h2><p>The adjustable buckle is now matte brass instead of nickel. Tighter tolerances, no more clinking against your sunglasses.</p><h2>Same cut</h2><p>Brushed cotton twill. Six-panel unstructured crown. Curved brim. Tonal embroidered logo.</p><h2>The colours</h2><p>Black, Cream, Cobalt. Pick one. Pick three.</p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "b0c1d2e3-f4a5-4789-90ab-cdef00000006",
      "title": "On Form: A Sprinter's Wardrobe",
      "slug": "on-form-a-sprinters-wardrobe",
      "category": "Athletes",
      "author": "Editorial Team",
      "featured": true,
      "readTime": 6,
      "publishedAt": "2026-04-15T15:00:00.000Z",
      "excerpt": "Three athletes, three definitions of form. The kit that survives both.",
      "description": "Three sprinters from the Jakarta Athletics Club on form, kit, and what they wear off-track.",
      "image": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1620799140188-3b2a02fd9a77?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1600",
      "content": "<p>We sat down with three sprinters to talk about form, kit, and what they actually wear when not training.</p><h2>On form</h2><p><em>Form is the smallest version of the right movement, repeated until it is the only version,</em> says Rina. You do not see it. You feel it.</p><h2>On kit</h2><p>All three named the same three pieces they wear off-track: a heavy hoodie, a relaxed track pant, a low-profile sneaker. <em>Performance fabric, civilian fit. That is the kit that survives both worlds,</em> Dewi said.</p><h2>On Volt</h2><p>The team has been wearing Volt for three seasons. The Pulse Low and the Pacer Hoodie get the most reps. The Atlas Tee, surprisingly, is the most photographed.</p>"
    }
  ]
}
